summary: Pride Of Jenni, the three-time Group 1 winner, has been retired after a lackluster performance in the Champions Mile at Flemington. The mare finished last in the race, prompting her connections to make the decision to retire her. The news came as a surprise to many, as Pride Of Jenni had been a consistent performer throughout her career. However, her recent form had been disappointing, and her last-place finish in the Champions Mile was the final straw. Pride Of Jenni's retirement marks the end of an era for Australian racing. She was one of the most popular horses in the country, and her achievements on the track were remarkable. She won 11 of her 22 starts, including the Caulfield Cup and the Cox Plate. Her retirement is a sad day for Australian racing, but she will always be remembered as one of the greats.
